<p>In its <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2000-06-30"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="06-30"><a href="/wiki/June_30" title="June 30">June 30</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/2000" title="2000">2000</a></span> annual report filed with the <a href="/wiki/Securities_and_Exchange_Commission" title="Securities and Exchange Commission" class="mw-redirect">SEC</a>, Seagram reported that Universal Music Group was responsible for 40% of worldwide <a href="/wiki/European_classical_music" title="European classical music" class="mw-redirect">classical music</a> sales over the preceding year.<sup id="cite_ref-8" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-8" title=""><span>[</span>9<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p><a name="Music_industry_organizations" id="Music_industry_organizations"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Music_industry&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: Music industry organizations">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Music industry organizations</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Academy_of_Country_Music" title="Academy of Country Music">Academy of Country Music</a> aka ACM</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Alliance_of_Artists_and_Recording_Companies" title="Alliance of Artists and Recording Companies">Alliance of Artists and Recording Companies</a> aka AARC</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/American_Federation_of_Musicians" title="American Federation of Musicians">American Federation of Musicians</a> aka <a href="/wiki/AFM" title="AFM">AFM</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/American_Federation_of_Television_and_Radio_Artists" title="American Federation of Television and Radio Artists">American Federation of Television and Radio Artists</a> aka <a href="/wiki/AFTRA" title="AFTRA" class="mw-redirect">AFTRA</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/American_Society_of_Composers,_Authors,_and_Publishers" title="American Society of Composers, Authors, and Publishers" class="mw-redirect">American Society of Composers, Authors, and Publishers</a> aka <a href="/wiki/ASCAP" title="ASCAP" class="mw-redirect">ASCAP</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Association_of_Independent_Music" title="Association of Independent Music">Association of Independent Music</a> aka <a href="/wiki/AIM" title="AIM">AIM</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Australian_Recording_Industry_Association" title="Australian Recording Industry Association">Australian Recording Industry Association</a> aka ARIA</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/British_Phonographic_Industry" title="British Phonographic Industry">British Phonographic Industry</a> (BPI)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Broadcast_Music_Incorporated" title="Broadcast Music Incorporated">Broadcast Music Incorporated</a> aka BMI</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Canadian_Recording_Industry_Association" title="Canadian Recording Industry Association">Canadian Recording Industry Association</a> (CRIA)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Country_Music_Association" title="Country Music Association">Country Music Association</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Federation_of_the_Italian_Music_Industry" title="Federation of the Italian Music Industry">Federation of the Italian Music Industry</a> (FIMI)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Gesellschaft_f%C3%BCr_musikalische_Auff%C3%BChrungs-_und_mechanische_Vervielf%C3%A4ltigungsrechte" title="Gesellschaft für musikalische Aufführungs- und mechanische Vervielfältigungsrechte">Gesellschaft für musikalische Aufführungs- und mechanische Vervielfältigungsrechte</a> (GEMA) in Germany</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Harry_Fox_Agency" title="Harry Fox Agency">Harry Fox Agency</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/International_Federation_of_the_Phonographic_Industry" title="International Federation of the Phonographic Industry" class="mw-redirect">International Federation of the Phonographic Industry</a> (IFPI)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Irish_Recorded_Music_Association" title="Irish Recorded Music Association">Irish Recorded Music Association</a> (IRMA)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Mechanical_Copyright_Protection_Society" title="Mechanical Copyright Protection Society" class="mw-redirect">MCPS</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Musicians%27_Union" title="Musicians' Union">Musicians' Union</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/National_Academy_of_Recording_Arts_and_Sciences" title="National Academy of Recording Arts and Sciences">National Academy of Recording Arts and Sciences</a> (NARAS)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/National_Association_of_Recording_Merchandisers" title="National Association of Recording Merchandisers">National Association of Recording Merchandisers</a> (NARM)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Performing_Right_Society" title="Performing Right Society" class="mw-redirect">Performing Right Society</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Recording_Artists%27_Coalition" title="Recording Artists' Coalition">Recording Artists' Coalition</a> aka RAC</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Recording_Industry_Association_of_America" title="Recording Industry Association of America">Recording Industry Association of America</a> (RIAA)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Recording_Industry_Association_of_New_Zealand" title="Recording Industry Association of New Zealand">Recording Industry Association of New Zealand</a> (RIANZ)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/SESAC" title="SESAC">SESAC</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/SoundExchange" title="SoundExchange">SoundExchange</a></li>
</ul>
